=== Tuplet ≠ Subdivision

We make a distinction between subdivisions and tuplets. Subdivisions divide the
beat and are therefore contained within the beat cycle. Tuplets, by contrast,
are considered as such — and distinguished from subdivisions — only when they
span a duration that is not a beat cycle, as is the case in a cross-rhythm.

Just as a pattern can be obtained by progressively swinging a subdivision
system, a tuplet can be obtained by progressively evening out a cross-rhythm
pattern. We can use that approach to access some difficult tuplet ratios such
